    <section id="id25422929">
      <title>Memorandum</title>
      <para id="id26370862">Observations:</para>
      <para id="id26390013">(i) The smoke rises.</para>
      <para id="id26367786">(ii) The smoke rises.</para>
      <para id="id26370398">(iii) The smoke rises.</para>
      <para id="id26371834">Conclusion:</para>
      <para id="id25679802">Hot air rises.</para>
      <para id="id26370873">During the day the land heats up more rapidly than the sea. The warm air above the land rises. Cooler air above the sea flows to the land to fill the place of the warm air. This is how sea winds originate.</para>
      <para id="id25382901">At night the land cools down more rapidly than the sea. Therefore the air above the sea is warmer and rises. Cooler air from above the land flows to the sea to take the place of the warmer air. This is how a land-wind (offshore wind) originates. </para>
    </section>
